The ''' Association of Thoracic and Cardiovascular Surgeons of Asia''' is an international association of [[Asia]]n [[Cardiothoracic surgeons]]. It was founded in 1972 by cardiothoracic surgeons in the Asian countries and its headquartered in [[Quezon City]], [[Philippines]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.vietnamplus.vn/vietnam-hosts-asian-congress-on-thoracic-cardiovascular-surgery/67889.vnp|title=Vietnam hosts Asian congress on thoracic, cardiovascular surgery |work=en.vietnamplus.vn|accessdate=January 9, 2015}}</ref> The association consists of members from 44 countries and to be considered for membership, a cardiothoracic surgeon must have a track record of distinction in the field and have made meritorious contributions to the knowledge of cardiothoracic disease and its surgical treatment.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://atcsa.org/council/|title= Association of Thoracic and Cardiovascular Surgeons of Asia|work=atcsa.org|accessdate=January 9, 2015}}</ref>
