'''''Kalmora, or The Paternal Right of the Americans'''''<ref name="Grove">''Jim Samson''. Kurpiński, Karol Kazimierz / [[Grove Dictionary of Music and Musicians]]</ref> ({{lang-pl|Kalmora, czyli prawo ojcowskie Amerykanów}}) – Polish opera (melodrama) in 2 acts by [[Karol Kurpiński]]. Libretto was written by [[Kazimierz Brodziński]]. Its first performance took place on 10 March 1820.<ref name="Brodz">{{cite book|last1=Brodziński|first1=K.|title=Kalmora, czyli prawo ojcowskie Amerykanów. Opera w 2 aktach heroiczno-pasterska, oryginalnie napisana z powieści amerykańskiej|date=1823}}</ref><ref>In Grove's dictionary the date is 10 February.</ref>

Complete score of the overture was published by [[Breitkopf & Härtel]] in [[Leipzig]] in 1825 or 1826<ref>[https://books.google.ru/books?id=L-EqAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA43 Intelligenz-Blatt zur AMZ 1826 No.1]</ref> as Kurpiński's Opus 14. Complete score of the whole opera (or at least some parts) is located in the library of [[Warszawskie Towarzystwo Muzyczne im. Stanisława Moniuszki]].<ref name="Grove" />

