{{Politics of Guinea-Bissau}}

The '''Manifest Party of the People''' ({{Lang-pt|Partido do Manifesto do Povo}}, PMP) is a [[political party]] in [[Guinea-Bissau]].

==History==
The PMP was established in 2003 by [[Faustino Imbali]].<ref name=HD>Peter Karibe Mendy (2013) ''Historical Dictionary of the Republic of Guinea-Bissau'', Scarecrow Press, p229</ref> The party received 0.8% of the vote in the [[Guinea-Bissau legislative election, 2004|2004 parliamentary elections]], failing to win a seat in the [[National People's Assembly (Guinea-Bissau)|National People's Assembly]]. Imbali was the party's candidate for the [[Guinea-Bissau presidential election, 2005|2005 presidential elections]], but received just 0.52% of the vote, finishing tenth in a field of 13 candidates.

The party did not contest elections in [[Guinea-Bissau legislative election, 2008|2008]], [[Guinea-Bissau presidential election, 2009|2009]] or [[Guinea-Bissau presidential election, 2012|2012]], but returned to active politics when it ran in the [[Guinea-Bissau general election, 2014|2014 parliamentary elections]]. It received 0.7% of the vote and failed to win a seat.

