{{Infobox military installation |name = Woodford's Battery |native_name = |partof = [[Fortifications of Gibraltar]] |location = [[Europa Point|Europa Flats]] |nearest_town = <!-- used in military test site infobox --> |country = [[Gibraltar]] |image = |alt = |caption = |image2 = <!--secondary image, major command emblems for airfields --> |alt2 = |caption2 = |type = [[Artillery battery]] |coordinates = {{coord|36.11085|-5.3496|type:landmark|display=inline}} |image_map = |image_mapsize = |image_map_alt = |image_map_caption = |pushpin_map = Gibraltar |pushpin_mapsize = |pushpin_map_alt = |pushpin_map_caption = Location within Gibraltar |pushpin_relief = |pushpin_image = |pushpin_label = |pushpin_label_position = |pushpin_mark = |pushpin_marksize = |ownership = [[Government of Gibraltar]] |operator = <!-- where different from ownership such as the RAF or the USAF --> |controlledby = <!-- such as RAF Bomber Command or the Eighth Air Force --> |open_to_public = Yes |site_other_label = <!-- for renaming "Other facilities" in infobox --> |site_other = <!-- for other sorts of facilities - radar types etc --> |area = <!-- area of site m2, km2 square mile etc --> |code = <!--facility/installation code, applies to US --> |built = |used = <!--{{End date|1946}} --> |builder = [[Ministry of Defence (United Kingdom)|UK Ministry of Defence]] |materials = |height = <!-- height of tallest part, not above sea level --> |fate = <!--changed from demolished parameter--> |condition = Abandoned |battles = |events = |commander = <!-- current commander --> |commanders = <!-- past notable commander(s) --> |garrison = <!-- such as the 25th Bombardment Group --> |occupants = <!-- squadrons only --> |website = |remediation = |image3 = |alt3 = |footnotes = <!-- catchall in case it's needed to preserve something in infobox that doesn't work in new code --> }} '''Woodford's Battery''' was an [[artillery battery]] in the [[British Overseas Territories|British Overseas Territory]] of [[Gibraltar]].<ref name="Finlayson2006">{{cite book|first1=Darren|last1=Fa|authorlink1=Darren Fa|first2=Clive|last2=Finlayson|authorlink2=Clive Finlayson|title=The Fortifications of Gibraltar 1068-1945|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BC5QBR0oB04C&pg=PA31|accessdate=4 April 2013|year=2006|publisher=Osprey Publishing|isbn=978-1-84603-016-1}}</ref> It is located at [[Europa Point|Europa Flats]] between the [[Defensible Barracks, Gibraltar|Defensible Barracks]] and the ''Officer's Barracks'' and [[Eliott's Battery]].<ref name=map1859>{{cite web|title=1859 Map of the Fortifications of Gibraltar|url=http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/78/1859_Gibraltar_fortifications_map.jpg|publisher=UK National Archives MPH 1/23|accessdate=14 May 2013}}</ref>
The battery was built before 1738 as a demi-bastion set into the old Spanish-era coastal wall, constructed by Charles V. It was originally called Five Gun Battery but its complement of guns was later expanded. It was equipped with four embrasures on the left flank, facing south-east towards Europa Point, and two on the right flank, facing north-west towards the nearby [[Hutment Battery]]. Further firing positions were provided a short distance further south by the three-gun Woodford's Left Flank battery, which together with the 1st Europa Point Right Flank battery [[Enfilade and defilade|enfiladed]] the ground in front of the Defensible Barracks. It was renamed after a [[governor of Gibraltar]], Field Marshal Sir [[Alexander George Woodford]], who served in that role between 1836–43.<ref name="Hughes383">{{cite book|title=Strong as the Rock of Gibraltar|last1=Hughes|first1=Quentin|last2=Migos|first2=Athanassios|publisher=Exchange Publications|year=1995|page=383}}</ref>
Nine guns had been installed in the battery by 1859 and it continued to mount a variety of guns up to 1892. During [[World War II]] it was used to mount a defence electric light, which was removed in the late 20th century.<ref name="Hughes383" />
